{
  "id": "L19_SP",
  "title": "Visita a casa de un amigo",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to handle a visit to a Spanish-speaking friend's house for the first time. We'll start with arriving and greeting your friend."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hola",
        "meaning": "Hello"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V01",
      "data": {
        "Un regalo": "A gift"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V02",
      "data": {
        "Vino": "Wine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V03",
      "data": {
        "Flores": "Flowers"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Esto es para ti",
        "meaning": "This is for you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¡Qué casa tan bonita!",
        "meaning": "What a nice house!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "casa",
        "phonetic": "/'kasa/",
        "tip": "The 's' sound in Spanish is always a sharp 's' sound, like in the English word 'see'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_SP_S01",
      "title": "Arriving at a Friend's Home",
      "setting": "You've just arrived at your friend Alex's house and are at the door.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet your friend",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Hola! ¡Bienvenido a mi casa!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Give your friend a gift",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Pasa, por favor! Me alegro de verte"
        },
        {
          "title": "Compliment their home",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Oh, muchas gracias! No era necesario"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now, let's learn how to have some small talk. Your friend will likely offer you something to drink."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Sí, por favor",
        "meaning": "Yes, please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V04",
      "data": {
        "Un café": "A coffee"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V05",
      "data": {
        "Un té": "A tea"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V06",
      "data": {
        "Agua": "Water"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Qué tal tu semana?",
        "meaning": "How was your week?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Puedo ayudar?",
        "meaning": "Can I help?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "semana",
        "phonetic": "/se'mana/",
        "tip": "In Spanish, the stress usually falls on the second-to-last syllable, as in 'se-MA-na'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_SP_S02",
      "title": "Having a Drink",
      "setting": "You are now sitting in your friend's living room.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Accept a drink and state your preference",
          "chatbot_message": "Gracias. Me gusta mucho. Toma asiento. ¿Quieres beber algo? ¿Un café o un té?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask how their week was",
          "chatbot_message": "Perfecto. Un café para ti"
        },
        {
          "title": "Offer to help",
          "chatbot_message": "Mi semana, bien. Mucho trabajo. ¿Y la tuya?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent! Finally, let's learn how to politely end the visit when it's time to go."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Es tarde",
        "meaning": "It's late"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_V07",
      "data": {
        "La noche": "The evening / The night"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Gracias por todo",
        "meaning": "Thanks for everything"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "noche",
        "phonetic": "/'notʃe/",
        "tip": "The Spanish 'ch' sound is just like the 'ch' in the English word 'cheese'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Adiós",
        "meaning": "Goodbye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_SP_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hasta luego",
        "meaning": "See you later"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_SP_S03",
      "title": "Leaving the House",
      "setting": "You've finished your drink and are ready to leave.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "State that it's getting late",
          "chatbot_message": "No, gracias. Tú eres mi invitado. Relájate"
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank your friend for the evening",
          "chatbot_message": "Sí, el tiempo pasa rápido"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "De nada. Gracias a ti por venir"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}